  "event": {
    "top_event": "Vessel collision with unmanned platform resulting in structural destruction and fire",
    "incident_type": "collision",
    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Three vessels in the area responded and assisted in extinguishing the fire",
      "BSEE and USCG were notified",
      "BSEE inspectors routinely flew over the site to monitor minor sheening and gas bubbling during first 1-2 weeks",
      "District supervisors held telephone conferences and office meetings with Energy XXI regarding debris clean-up, diving, and abandonment operations",
      "Mobile jack-up rig Hercules 205 arrived on location on 03-March-2015 for plug and abandonment operations"
    ],
    "summary": "At approximately 0430 hours on 23-January-2015, an offshore supply vessel struck an unmanned Energy XXI production platform at OCSG 1443, South Timbalier 27 IA. Ninety percent of the structure was destroyed as a result of the collision and subsequent fire. The platform had three producing gaslift wells with average daily production of 92 barrels of oil, 93 barrels of water, and 115 million cubic feet of gas per day.",
